As it stands, simply installing the addon does not affect current functionality, only Admins can see the scripts etc via the Admin panel if they so chose. 

Already merged with previous PRs changes re: product versions

Commit history:

*  updating crowd / confluence / bb / bam / fecru

* added scriptrunner install to product xml and updated dbs with licenses

* rolling back bitbucket due to illegal arg in upm check this time from master

* fixing db issue

* removing bb manual dl as it appears it doesn't need it

* moved plugin download to shared directory and updated db

content.raw:
I'm assuming TIS runs up all the different products at different context paths, likely with some type of reverse proxy in front so that even though they're in separate servlet containers they look like a single instance. In that type of setup, where all the products have the same hostname and just different context paths, if you don't change the session cookies you get conflicts, where, for example, logging into JIRA logs you out of Bitbucket Server.

That said, this really might be something it makes sense for the products to \_ship\_ with. But since they don't, you need to do it.

summary.html:
This will be a destructive fix, as it renders our ability to do the current date-hack impossible (as H2 is a binary db).
